As a US Citizen, can I bring my uncles, aunts, cousins, nephews and nieces from Mexico? If you are a US Citizen you may petition for the following foreign national relatives to immigrate to the United States; however you must be able to provide proof of the relationships:

* Husband or wife;
* Unmarried child under 21 years old;
* Unmarried son or daughter over 21;
* Married son or daughter of any age;
* Brother or sister, if you are at least 21 years old; or
* Parent, if you are at least 21 years old.

